reviews.text:
Good variety of food. Duck noodles, western food, muslim food are good.
Drinks stall service poor. Pay attention to the cashier machine if you are making large orders, they might sneak in additional charges for items not ordered.
Drinks shop uncle sitting in front of fan and smoking in dining area.

Inside this canteen there's this noodle food stall i will highly recommend. Food is so nice and much to my likings. Patronize this stall regularly. Today tried it's wanton noodles and it taste super good while pricing is economical. Must try! è¶…èµž! ðŸ˜‹ ðŸ˜‹ ðŸ˜‹

Order the mixed mutton soup from the China ä¸œåŒ— stall. It was the most horrible mutton soup I taste . The soup is tasteless and the mix mutton was so staunch that u can't even swallow. This lesson tell me to keep to local food.

New eatery in the area that's newly opened. Convenient and not stuffy. Please avoid the economic rice stall. Overcharging for a plate of one vegetables and one meat. Claims that lotus root is meat. The seller needs to be re-schooled to learn the difference meat and vegetables. The economic beehoon need to avoid mixing of noodles, else there's an extra surcharge of $0.50. Still trying to figure out the feedback of other stalls!

Disappointed with the Western stall. Manu pic shows 1 full slice chicken cost $6.50... When serve, was not even half slice of the chop. Ask the stall lady and her answer was "Display is picture only." The spagatti not tasty at all. Don't waste time. Try other stalls.
